  sodium: 4.2 g
  serving size: 658
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/teriyaki-salmon-tacos-5d9de8156e3fd93cf00a8376
servings: 2
course: main course
author: Mimi Morley
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1/2}(thinly sliced). Put the @Rice Vinegar{15%ml} into a #bowl{} and add the @Sugar for the Pickle{1%tbsp}. Stir together, then add the red onion. Stir to thoroughly coat the onion in the pickling liquor, then leave to the side until the end.

> TIP: Give the onion an extra toss to coat every now and then.

Chop the @Sweet Potato{1} into chips the length and thickness of your index finger (no need to peel). Pop the chips onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle with a little @oil{}, and season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Arrange them in a single layer and pop them onto the top shelf of the oven to cook until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Lay the @Salmon Fillets{2} on a baking tray skin-side down. Season with salt and pepper. Roast the salmon for ~{15%minutes}. Once cooked, remove to a #board{} skin side up, allow to cool a little, then peel off (and discard) the skin. Pop the salmon into a bowl gently pull apart into flakes. Set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw fish.

Meanwhile, heat a #saucepan{} on medium heat and add the @Sesame Seeds{15%g}(no oil). Toast them until golden, ~{2%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat and set aside (we'll use later.) Divide the sesame seeds between 2 separate #medium bowls{}. Add the @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp} to one of the bowls along with the @water{25%ml}. Season with salt and pepper. Stir together, set aside.

Add the @Soy Sauce{25%ml}, @Honey{15%ml}, and @Ketjap Manis{25%ml} to the saucepan, pop back on medium heat and simmer until thick and sticky, ~{3-5%minutes}. Stir in the sesame seeds and set aside. Meanwhile, trim the root from the @Baby Gem Lettuce{1} then half length ways. Thinly slice widthways, add the baby gem to the sesame mayo dressing and toss to coat. Set aside. Add the teriyaki sauce to the salmon and gently stir to combine.

Add the @Plain Taco Tortillas{6} to the oven for ~{2-3%minutes} to warm through. Spread the lettuce salad on the base of each taco (3 per person), then add the teriyaki salmon. Finish with the onion pickle. Serve the sweet potato chips alongside and enjoy!